 satin slip dress cardigan Photo @lefevrediary Satin slip dresses are in style right now, but with every trendy fashion item, there’s the problem of standing out in the crowd when everyone’s wearing the same thing.   So how do you fix this? Finding new creative, and stylish ways to pull off your satin slip dress allows you to look stylish each time. These are 5 creative ways to style your satin slip dresses: A good layer takes even the simplest outfit and makes it look its best every time. Style your satin slip dresses with layers for a more casual look, think chunky knits, hooded sweatshirts, and blazers. You can also layer underneath with long-sleeved tops and tights. Trust us when we say this style trend makes all the difference. Slip dress coat Okay, granted, slip dresses are delicate and feminine, which is what most people try to pull off every time they wear one. To transform your feminine look with contrast, we’re thinking leather boots and chokers for a more gritty contrast. Alternatively, think colour blocking. slip dress sneakers Gen z readers most definitely understand the importance of a good athleisure aesthetic. Pair your lace-trimmed slip dress with a pair of sneakers and your favourite hoodie for the effortlessly chic, cool-girl finish. Blazer and satin slip dress Photo @lenafarl Who says slip-dresses can’t make it into work? Well, we think you can absolutely pull them off whenever, wherever. Think oversized blazers, layered tights and a pair of heels. Style satin slip dresses cardigan satin slip dress We love a good accessory moment; the right shoes, bags, and jewellery make a lot of difference in fashion. To style your satin slip dresses, consider adding a belt, some jewellery and the right hand back.